timing_report_constraint_format(25.10)  timing_report_constraint_format(25.10)

Name
       timing_report_constraint_format

Syntax
       timing_report_constraint_format <string >

       Default: " "

       Specifies  the  DRV  fields  that will be reported with the report_con-
       straint command. For valid format column options, refer to  report_con-
       straint -drv_fields.

       If  DRV fields are not specified with this global variable (or with re-
       port_constraint -drv_fields), then the default set of DRV  fields  will
       be  displayed.  By  default, the constraint report will display the pin
       names, the required and actual DRC values, and the view names.

       Note:  The  reporting  fields  specified  with  the   report_constraint
       -drv_fields parameter will override the global variable settings.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

